Currently the error that happens deals with nil and is accurate,
but not necessarily helpful to someone working with this class.

Instead, we can check and raise (or use fail if we are
purposefully failing) and give good information to the user to
help them deal with this.

```
Please enter your letters: banana*s

Exception `NoMethodError' at /home/vgoff/mentoring/andrew_baldwin/scrabble/lib/tile.rb:29 - undefined method `[]' for nil:NilClass
undefined method `[]' for nil:NilClass
Your word must only contain valid tiles
```
